00:10:45,269 --> 00:10:47,563
<i>While Janet was handcuffing Chris,</i>

236
00:10:47,647 --> 00:10:50,566
<i>a bunch of demons must've grabbed Michael,</i>
<i>yanked him away,</i>

237
00:10:50,650 --> 00:10:53,986
<i>and then Vicky, in the Michael suit,</i>
<i>walked back out.</i>

238
00:10:54,070 --> 00:10:55,655
<i>You never would have known the difference.</i>

239
00:10:55,738 --> 00:10:58,991
<i>Also, when Chris got back,</i>
<i>I saw Shawn and him celebrating. </i>

240
00:10:59,075 --> 00:11:01,786
<i>Why would they be happy</i>
<i>if he wasn't supposed to get caught?</i>

241
00:11:01,869 --> 00:11:03,954
Man, I love a good sabotage.

242
00:11:04,038 --> 00:11:06,707
Or is that exactly
what you want us to think?

243
00:11:06,791 --> 00:11:08,000
[Eleanor] Motherforker.

244
00:11:08,084 --> 00:11:10,461
I knew there was something
weird about that puncher.

245
00:11:10,544 --> 00:11:12,129
I said that to Michael...

246
00:11:13,297 --> 00:11:14,548
and he dismissed it.

247
00:11:14,632 --> 00:11:17,843
-[speaks gibberish] See what I mean?
-Don't go anywhere.

248
00:11:17,927 --> 00:11:18,886
Come on.

249
00:11:20,888 --> 00:11:23,224
If Michael is just Vicky
in a Michael suit,

250
00:11:23,307 --> 00:11:24,433
let's just take the suit off.

251
00:11:24,517 --> 00:11:27,895
Yeah, maybe we can sneak up behind him
and try and pants him from the forehead.

252
00:11:27,978 --> 00:11:28,896
That won't work.

253
00:11:28,979 --> 00:11:31,857
A demon can take his own skin suit off,
but no one else can.

254
00:11:31,941 --> 00:11:33,984
It's like a very complicated bra.

255
00:11:34,068 --> 00:11:36,570
Well, so be it.

256
00:11:36,654 --> 00:11:37,822
[door opens]

257
00:11:38,406 --> 00:11:40,157
Take off your skin suit.

258
00:11:41,534 --> 00:11:43,244
-I can't.
-Sure, you can.

259
00:11:43,327 --> 00:11:46,330
You're either a demon wearing
a Michael suit,

260
00:11:46,414 --> 00:11:51,627
or you're a demon wearing a Vicky suit,
who's wearing a Michael suit over that.

261
00:11:51,710 --> 00:11:55,548
Just take off your Michael suit
and show us what you're working with.

262
00:11:55,631 --> 00:11:57,967
I'm sorry, I won't.

263
00:11:58,050 --> 00:11:59,885
-That's very suspicious.
-I know.

264
00:11:59,969 --> 00:12:01,095
But I'm not Vicky.

265
00:12:01,178 --> 00:12:03,347
I just don't want to show you
what's underneath here.

266
00:12:03,431 --> 00:12:05,766
I've seen a lot of weird hogs
in my life, dude.

267
00:12:05,850 --> 00:12:06,767
Get over yourself.

268
00:12:06,851 --> 00:12:08,269
That's not it.

269
00:12:10,187 --> 00:12:11,772
I'm a fire squid.

270
00:12:12,940 --> 00:12:14,191
Dope.

271
00:12:14,275 --> 00:12:17,069
No, not dope.

272
00:12:17,987 --> 00:12:21,824
I'm a 6,000-foot tall fire squid.

273
00:12:21,907 --> 00:12:25,870
I have tentacles.
There's teeth everywhere.

274
00:12:25,953 --> 00:12:32,585
I'm on fire, and my neck is long,
and there's a smell and lots of juice.

275
00:12:32,668 --> 00:12:35,045
[breathing heavily]
There's so much juice, Eleanor.

276
00:12:35,129 --> 00:12:38,841
I think I speak for everyone here
when I say...

277
00:12:38,924 --> 00:12:40,718
I really have to see this.

278
00:12:40,801 --> 00:12:45,764
So, you're not gonna take off
your demon Spanx because you're shy?

279
00:12:45,848 --> 00:12:47,683
That's convenient.

280
00:12:47,766 --> 00:12:51,604
Eleanor, if I take off this suit,
I will crash through the roof,

281
00:12:51,687 --> 00:12:55,900
and the entire neighborhood will see me,
and the experiment will be blown.

282
00:12:56,609 --> 00:12:57,693
But it's more than that.

283
00:12:57,776 --> 00:13:00,613
You guys will never look at me
the same way again.

284
00:13:00,696 --> 00:13:03,365
I won't just be Michael.

285
00:13:03,449 --> 00:13:09,997
I'll be some disgusting mass
of burning tentacles.

286
00:13:10,873 --> 00:13:13,751
Do you really wanna be friends
with something like that?

287
00:13:13,834 --> 00:13:15,753
Yes! I keep saying.

288
00:13:15,836 --> 00:13:17,129
Eleanor.

289
00:13:18,839 --> 00:13:20,466
Now, I don't know if this will work,

290
00:13:20,549 --> 00:13:23,219
but, theoretically,
if you point it at a demon and he's lying,

291
00:13:23,302 --> 00:13:24,637
it'll turn red.

292
00:13:24,720 --> 00:13:26,138
If he's telling the truth,
it'll turn green.

293
00:13:26,222 --> 00:13:27,056
[Eleanor] Okay.

294
00:13:28,015 --> 00:13:32,478
Glenn, this is a lie detector.
Let us show you how it works.

295
00:13:32,561 --> 00:13:33,521
[lie detector hums]

296
00:13:33,604 --> 00:13:34,688
What's your name?

297
00:13:34,772 --> 00:13:36,857
Well, everyone calls me Glenn,

298
00:13:36,941 --> 00:13:42,696
but the name on my demon certificate
is actually Snakes Pour Forth From His--

299
00:13:44,698 --> 00:13:47,201
[Janet and Tahani exclaiming]

300
00:13:47,284 --> 00:13:49,662
Glenn blew up. Glenn blew up.

301
00:13:49,745 --> 00:13:52,790
Or is that exactly
what he wants us to think?

302
00:13:57,586 --> 00:14:00,506
So, does blowing up mean
he was telling the truth or lying?

303
00:14:00,589 --> 00:14:04,134
Neither. That was not supposed to happen.
I've never killed anybody before.

304
00:14:04,218 --> 00:14:06,387
No, don't worry, demons can't die.

305
00:14:06,470 --> 00:14:09,807
He'll slowly re-form himself
over a few months,

306
00:14:09,890 --> 00:14:12,977
passing through
all the stages of demon growth:

307
00:14:13,060 --> 00:14:17,439
larva, slug monster,
spooky little girl, teenage boy,

308
00:14:17,523 --> 00:14:19,608
giant ball of tongues,

309
00:14:19,692 --> 00:14:23,362
social media CEO,
and then finally, demon.

310
00:14:23,445 --> 00:14:26,156
So, look at the bright side.
This worked out perfectly.

311
00:14:26,740 --> 00:14:31,120
I mean, not for Glenn, obviously,
but for us.

312
00:14:31,203 --> 00:14:33,914
The lying demon's gone.
We're still here. All good.

313
00:14:33,998 --> 00:14:37,126
No. We're not "all good," man.

314
00:14:37,209 --> 00:14:41,130
You're either Michael and you lied,
or you're Vicky in a Michael suit.

315
00:14:41,213 --> 00:14:44,633
Okay, I'm gonna go for a walk.
Nobody go anywhere.

316
00:14:50,306 --> 00:14:52,308
-Chidi?
-Hey.

317
00:14:52,391 --> 00:14:54,768
Hey. I didn't think
anyone would still be up.

318
00:14:56,729 --> 00:14:57,855
Are you okay?

319
00:14:57,938 --> 00:14:59,064
Uh, yeah, yeah.

320
00:14:59,148 --> 00:15:03,736
Um, I'm just practicing
drawing viable horses.

321
00:15:03,819 --> 00:15:07,448
Ones that aren't crimes against nature.

322
00:15:07,531 --> 00:15:09,283
Okay, I know this mood of yours.

323
00:15:10,284 --> 00:15:12,745
From reading your file and whatnot.

324
00:15:12,828 --> 00:15:17,249
Um, why don't you take a break
and we'll get some food in you?

325
00:15:19,960 --> 00:15:21,420
[Janet] Well, I'm done.

326
00:15:21,503 --> 00:15:24,256
I scooped it all up into
one steaming pile of Glenn.

327
00:15:24,340 --> 00:15:27,468
Maybe I can put him back together.
I'm hella good at puzzles.

328
00:15:27,551 --> 00:15:30,346
I finished this word search in 30 seconds.

329
00:15:30,429 --> 00:15:31,805
[Janet] Jason, I feel terrible.

330
00:15:31,889 --> 00:15:34,683
I know he was a demon,
and he may have lied to us,

331
00:15:34,767 --> 00:15:36,894
but he didn't deserve that.

332
00:15:36,977 --> 00:15:38,479
You were only trying to help us.

333
00:15:38,562 --> 00:15:41,815
Look, I know this is a weird time,

334
00:15:41,899 --> 00:15:44,902
but if you ever wanna talk,
just know that I'm here for you, girl.

335
00:15:45,569 --> 00:15:49,323
Thanks, Jason. That means a lot.

336
00:15:54,119 --> 00:15:56,872
Mmm! I gotta say,

337
00:15:56,956 --> 00:16:00,292
out of all the "human stuff" I've been
able to experience in this neighborhood,

338
00:16:00,376 --> 00:16:02,878
nachos? Number one. Easy.

339
00:16:02,962 --> 00:16:03,837
Really?

340
00:16:03,921 --> 00:16:05,297
Yeah.

341
00:16:05,381 --> 00:16:10,177
I mean, salty, crunchy, cheesy,
little bit of a kick.

342
00:16:10,260 --> 00:16:12,554
Name one better thing humans have created.

343
00:16:12,638 --> 00:16:15,391
-The Sistine Chapel?
-Pfft! Paint on a ceiling.

344
00:16:15,474 --> 00:16:18,435
I mean, it's fine,
but can you eat it at the movies?

345
00:16:18,519 --> 00:16:19,979
TouchÃ©.

346
00:16:20,062 --> 00:16:23,774
Listen, don't stay up all night
drawing horses. It's really fine.

347
00:16:23,857 --> 00:16:29,613
I know. I just feel like
I made the world a little bit worse,

348
00:16:30,197 --> 00:16:33,283
and I won't be okay
until I make it better again.

349
00:16:33,367 --> 00:16:37,538
Making yourself miserable
to ease the suffering of others.

350
00:16:37,621 --> 00:16:39,623
About the most Chidi thing you can do.

351
00:16:41,125 --> 00:16:42,668
I'll see you later.

352
00:16:44,920 --> 00:16:46,672
Do you wanna take
the rest of those nachos with you?

353
00:16:46,755 --> 00:16:47,965
Yeah, I do, thank you.

354
00:16:50,843 --> 00:16:54,513
Okay, here's where I'm at.
I just don't know if I can ever trust you.

355
00:16:54,596 --> 00:16:57,307
I'm gonna call the Judge.
We'll start over.

356
00:16:57,391 --> 00:17:00,185
We won't have Chidi in the mix,
but he'll be on our side again,

357
00:17:00,269 --> 00:17:01,979
which is almost as good.

358
00:17:02,062 --> 00:17:03,522
But we know the humans now.

359
00:17:03,605 --> 00:17:06,567
-Starting over sounds exhausting.
-[Eleanor] I know.

360
00:17:06,650 --> 00:17:07,943
But if that's not Michael,

361
00:17:08,027 --> 00:17:11,447
he could sabotage us
in ways we can't even perceive.

362
00:17:11,530 --> 00:17:14,158
And even if it is,
I can't fully trust him,

363
00:17:14,241 --> 00:17:18,245
so every time something goes wrong,
a little part of me is gonna wonder.

364
00:17:19,288 --> 00:17:20,164
We have to start over.

365
00:17:21,165 --> 00:17:22,624
I have a better idea.

366
00:17:23,333 --> 00:17:25,461
-I'm gonna blow myself up.
-[Tahani and Eleanor] What?

367
00:17:25,544 --> 00:17:26,628
I'll blow myself up.

368
00:17:26,712 --> 00:17:30,340
That way, you can continue the experiment
with Chidi as one of the people,

369
00:17:30,424 --> 00:17:33,510
which is our best chance
to ever be successful.

370
00:17:33,594 --> 00:17:37,222
Why not just lock you in a room,
or in Janet's void or something?

371
00:17:37,306 --> 00:17:39,475
But then you might worry that I'd escape.

372
00:17:39,558 --> 00:17:41,477
If I blow myself up,
I'm out of your hair for good.

373
00:17:41,560 --> 00:17:45,939
Well, parts of me will be
in your actual hair, but you get it.

374
00:17:46,023 --> 00:17:48,859
-Michael, wait--
-Tahani, this is the only way.

375
00:17:48,942 --> 00:17:51,820
There's literally nothing I can say
that will make you realize

376
00:17:51,904 --> 00:17:53,572
that I'm really me.

377
00:17:54,615 --> 00:17:56,408
Oh, boy. This is gonna suck.

378
00:17:56,492 --> 00:17:59,244
Hopefully, I will see you all
in a few months. Good luck.

379
00:17:59,328 --> 00:18:03,707
Oh, and make sure you, uh,
get all of me into the container,

380
00:18:03,791 --> 00:18:09,129
or I might come back, uh, way shorter,
and that would bum me out.

381
00:18:09,213 --> 00:18:10,547
[lie detector hums]

382
00:18:10,631 --> 00:18:14,802
I wish I were saying this
in different circumstances, but...

383
00:18:16,762 --> 00:18:17,805
take it sleazy.

384
00:18:17,888 --> 00:18:18,972
[Jason] Michael, wait!

385
00:18:21,558 --> 00:18:24,144
Oh, crud-nuts!

386
00:18:25,938 --> 00:18:28,565
Jason, how did you know
that was Bad Janet?

387
00:18:28,649 --> 00:18:30,692
Michael said there's nothing he could say

388
00:18:30,776 --> 00:18:32,903
that would make you realize
he's really him.

389
00:18:32,986 --> 00:18:35,280
But Janet does have a thing she can say

390
00:18:35,364 --> 00:18:38,117
that does make me realize
she is really not her.

391
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:39,409
What?

392
00:18:39,493 --> 00:18:42,204
I called Janet "girl,"
but she didn't say "not a girl."

393
00:18:42,287 --> 00:18:45,374
The real Janet always says "not a girl."

394
00:18:46,250 --> 00:18:47,876
[gasps] Oh, wow.

395
00:18:48,544 --> 00:18:52,381
That realization's the only thing that
stopped me from becoming a pile of goo.

396
00:18:52,464 --> 00:18:53,423
-Ugh.
-[Tahani] Ugh!

397
00:18:53,507 --> 00:18:55,008
[Eleanor] Wait, how did you pull it off?

398
00:18:55,092 --> 00:18:57,261
You were outside on the platform with me
the whole time.

399
00:18:57,344 --> 00:19:01,557
We brought two Bad Janets on the train,
you dumb, dumb idiot.

400
00:19:01,640 --> 00:19:04,101
<i>The other one </i>
<i>distracted you on the platform</i>

401
00:19:04,184 --> 00:19:06,478
<i>while Good Janet brought Chris </i>
<i>on to the train.</i>

402
00:19:06,562 --> 00:19:11,150
<i>I snuck out, marbleized Janet</i>
<i>and then I took over, baby.</i>

403
00:19:11,233 --> 00:19:13,193
<i>Stupid Michael never knew.</i>

404
00:19:13,277 --> 00:19:15,863
I had you fart-knockers fooled for weeks.

405
00:19:15,946 --> 00:19:20,325
Until Glenn, the traitor,
ruined everything. That guy sucks, right?

406
00:19:20,409 --> 00:19:23,120
-[squelches]
-Shut up, Glenn.

407
00:19:23,203 --> 00:19:26,707
Wait, wait, wait. Bad Janets can't
impersonate Good Janets.

408
00:19:26,790 --> 00:19:28,542
I've seen them try.
Their heads melt, so...

409
00:19:28,625 --> 00:19:30,836
Oh. Oh, you're so smart, sir.

410
00:19:30,919 --> 00:19:34,965
Well, listen, here's the thing.
Shawn rebooted me 40 million tines.

411
00:19:35,507 --> 00:19:38,677
Wait, tine-mis. Timeses.

412
00:19:39,344 --> 00:19:40,929
These things rule.

413
00:19:41,013 --> 00:19:44,391
Oh, dip, this means Janet didn't dump me.
Her weird sister did!

414
00:19:44,474 --> 00:19:46,518
Everything makes so much more sense.

415
00:19:46,602 --> 00:19:49,521
All of Janet's ideas
were so counterproductive.

416
00:19:49,605 --> 00:19:51,398
She brought the horse monster to life.

417
00:19:51,481 --> 00:19:54,109
She forced me to antagonize John.

418
00:19:54,193 --> 00:19:57,404
She got us to doubt
Eleanor's leadership skills.

419
00:19:57,487 --> 00:19:59,406
Oh, I was just about to launch an idea

420
00:19:59,489 --> 00:20:01,992
where Tahani was gonna give herself
an asymmetrical haircut.

421
00:20:02,576 --> 00:20:05,329
{\an8}-You monster.
-Thank you.

422
00:20:05,412 --> 00:20:07,331
{\an8}Guys, we still have a problem here.

423
00:20:07,414 --> 00:20:09,833
{\an8}You still don't have evidence
that I'm actually me.

424
00:20:09,917 --> 00:20:11,210
{\an8}Sure, we do.

425
00:20:11,293 --> 00:20:13,921
{\an8}You offered to sacrifice yourself
to help a bunch of cockroaches.

426
00:20:15,547 --> 00:20:17,299
{\an8}That's about the most Michael thing
you can do.

427
00:20:18,675 --> 00:20:20,427
{\an8}Where's real Janet?

428
00:20:20,510 --> 00:20:22,179
{\an8}[laughs] Oh, she's in the Bad Place.

429
00:20:22,262 --> 00:20:25,766
{\an8}She's probably wiping her butt
with her own butt. [laughs]

430
00:20:25,849 --> 00:20:29,853
{\an8}I can't bear the idea of poor Janet
down there, all alone.

431
00:20:30,729 --> 00:20:32,105
{\an8}[sighs] What should we do?

432
00:20:32,689 --> 00:20:34,441
I know what to do.

433
00:20:34,524 --> 00:20:36,818
It's like what that guy
who blew up said...

434
00:20:37,861 --> 00:20:39,738
Shawn's a bully.

435
00:20:39,821 --> 00:20:44,159
And sometimes the only thing a bully
understands is a punch in the mouth.

436
00:20:44,910 --> 00:20:48,163
I'm gonna go down there,
I'm gonna punch him in the mouth

437
00:20:48,247 --> 00:20:50,666
and I'm gonna get Janet back.

438
00:20:50,749 --> 00:20:53,085
[exclaims] Sounds like
somebody has a plan.

439
00:20:53,168 --> 00:20:54,044
Dope.

440
00:20:54,127 --> 00:20:56,255
Uh, where is he? What's the plan?

441
00:20:56,338 --> 00:20:57,714
It's okay.

442
00:21:00,676 --> 00:21:03,762
-You sure you can hold down the fort?
-Not at all.

443
00:21:03,845 --> 00:21:06,139
-You sure you can do your thing?
-Nope.

444
00:21:07,015 --> 00:21:08,976
We'll just try our best, right?

445
00:21:10,310 --> 00:21:12,229
Okay. Let's go get our girl.

446
00:21:12,813 --> 00:21:14,273
Not a girl.
